jei.caf.info.knife: Knives are lightweight melee weapons. They can harvest Straw from grasses, and guarantee secondary drops from animals.
jei.caf.text.fragile.destroy: Fragile. Ingredient will be destroyed on wrong speed
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_1: Since this smelter works according to a different scheme, different from Minecraft’s, its operating principle is as follows:
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_2: By putting fuel in the fuel cell you will raise the heat level to a certain level. For example, blaze cake will raise the heat level by 1000°C
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_3: To remelt the metal, you need to observe the melting degree
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_4: If the melting degree is lower than required, the process will not be performed
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_5: And if the melting degree is more than required, the process will be performed faster
caf.ponder.blast_furnace.text_6: The main thing is to remember that the smelting furnace will cool down over time
caf.ponder.cog_speedup.text_1: Large and Small cogs can be connected diagonally
caf.ponder.cog_speedup.text_2: Shifting from large to small cogs, the conveyed speed will be doubled
caf.ponder.cog_speedup.text_3: Shifting the opposite way, the conveyed speed will be halved
caf.ponder.fermentation_barrel_connect.t: As you can see, Fermentation Barrel is not connected by height
As you may have noticed Fermentation Barrel does not connect 2x2
As you may have noticed Fermentation Barrel does not connect 3x3
caf.ponder.fermentation_barrel_connect_p: Connect Fermentation Barrel with a pipe
You can see that only the pipe at the top was connected
You can only pour in liquid, but you can't pump it out
caf.ponder.fermentation_barrel_placing_i: In Fermentation Barrel you can place items through the auxiliary blocks, but you can't place items through the top
You can see the item fits into Fermentation Barrel
caf.ponder.large_steel_cogwheel.header: Relaying rotational force using Large Steel Cogwheels
caf.ponder.large_steel_cogwheel.text_1: Large cogwheels can connect to each other at right angles
caf.ponder.large_steel_cogwheel.text_2: It will help relaying conveyed speed to other axes of rotation
caf.ponder.mechanical_blender.header: Processing Items with the Mechanical Blender
caf.ponder.mechanical_blender.text_1: With a Blender and Basin, some Crafting Recipes can be automated
caf.ponder.mechanical_blender.text_2: Available recipes include any Cutting Crafting Recipe, plus a couple extra ones
caf.ponder.mechanical_blender.text_3: Some of those recipes may require the heat of a Blaze Burner
caf.ponder.mechanical_blender.text_4: The filter slot can be used in case two recipes are conflicting.
caf.ponder.scales.text_1: To start weighing, you need to put the item on the scales
caf.ponder.scales.text_2: Then right-click on the scales with an empty hand
caf.ponder.scales.text_4: To remove the item from the scales, you need to click
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel.header: Relaying rotational force using Steel Cogwheels
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel.text_1: Steel Cogwheels will relay rotation to other adjacent cogwheels
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel.text_2: Neighbouring shafts connected like this will rotate in opposite directions
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel_casing.text_1: Steel Block, Secure Block, Andesite and Brass Casings can be used to decorate Cogwheels
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel_casing.text_2: Components added after encasing will not connect to the shaft outputs
caf.ponder.steel_cogwheel_casing.text_3: The Wrench can be used to toggle connections
caf.ponder.steel_shaft.header: Relaying rotational force using Steel Shafts
caf.ponder.steel_shaft.text_1: Shafts will relay rotation in a straight line.
caf.ponder.steel_shaft_casing.text_1: Steel Block, Secure Block, Andesite and Brass Casings can be used to decorate Shafts
caf.ponder.terrace_all.text_1: Terraces come in different types of wood, as well as terrace stairs
caf.ponder.terrace_connect.text_1: Can be connected into 2 blocks in height
caf.ponder.terrace_connect.text_2: Can be connected into 3 blocks in height, but they can do more
caf.ponder.terrace_connect.text_4: Can be connected into 2 blocks in height
caf.ponder.terrace_connect.text_5: Can be connected into 3 blocks in height, but they can do more
caf.ponder.terrace_connect.text_7: If you have a limited number of Terrace stairs then you can use the blocks in this way
caf.ponder.terminal.text_1: Having placed the ingot in Terminal for Metal Samples can you find out more information about the ingot
caf.ponder.terminal.text_2: In Terminal for Metal Samples can put any identified metal
